BSP Marker requires:

MAXs BBS or /X\ Pro
MagicFile 3.0+


@{"  Back to main menu...  " link MAIN}
@ENDNODE
@NODE Install "ˇNSTALLING bSP mARKER 1.oo"
----------[ ˇNSTALLATION ]--------------------------------------------------

Installation of BSP Marker is very easy.  Just copy the file to the place of
your choice.. and keep this help guide for handy reference.

It would be a good idea to place BSP Marker somewhere where you can quickly
access it from Workbench.. althought you can also start the program from the
CLI :)


@{"  Back to main menu...  " link MAIN}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Usage "uSAGE oF bSP mARKER"
----------[ uSAGE oF bSP mARKER ]-------------------------------------------

Usage of BSP Marker is very easy.  Just start the program, by either
clicking on the icon from Workbench, or from the CLI.  You will be guided
through the program by a set of GUIs.  All you have to do is follow the
instructions through the program in order to mark what you need to mark.

* You don't even HAVE to use the mouse in this program :)) *

You can use the return key, or the mouse to progress through the parts of
thr program.. where there is more then one answer, you can use hotkeys :)

eg:
 _____________________________________________________
|                                                     |
|   Ok                                     No Way!    |
|   -                                      -          |
|_____________________________________________________|

This would let you press RightAmiga-O for OK, or N for No Way!

@{u}The File Requestor@{uu}

This lets you type a pattern to match, and specify a path and filename..
however.. you MUST stay in BBS:Files/ and the file MUST be online for this
to work.

Then just select the file to mark :)


- You can cancel any marking at the end of the program..


@{"  Back to main menu...  " link MAIN}

@ENDNODE

